<subSubSection id="38FC94CD9A17B11FFC80F88F63EEFDE4" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="7059C7469A17B11FFC80F88F63D4FDD0" blockId="40.[826,1441,1819,1903]" lastBlockId="41.[144,759,198,587]" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName id="B7E6BCC59A17B11EFC80F88F6644F8CB" authority="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo, 2014" authorityName="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo" authorityYear="2014" box="[826,1035,1851,1872]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teresae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="42921B549A17B11EFC80F88F6644F8CB" box="[826,1035,1851,1872]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">Notopoma teresae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="59A1A62F9A17B11EFBA8F88F6628F8CB" box="[1042,1127,1851,1872]" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B7E6BCC59A17B11EFA9AF88F6611F8F4" authority="Lowry &amp; Berents, 1996" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Berents" authorityYear="1996" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="42921B549A17B11EFA9AF88F67EEF8D4" box="[1312,1441,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">N. africana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1477BAB79A17B11EFC80F8ED6611F8F4" author="Lowry JK &amp; Berents PB" box="[826,1118,1881,1903]" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" pagination="75 - 109" refId="ref31067" refString="Lowry JK, Berents PB. 1996. The Ericthonius group, a new perspective on an old problem (Crustacea: Amphipoda: Corophioidea). Records of the Australian Museum 48: 75 - 109." type="journal article" year="1996">Lowry &amp; Berents, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B7E6BCC59A17B11FFB12F8ED6280FF47" authority="(Lowry, 1981)" baseAuthorityName="Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="1981" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" order="Amphipoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallohidea">
<emphasis id="42921B549A17B11EFB12F8ED6773F8F5" box="[1192,1340,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="74">N. fallohidea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1477BAB79A17B11FFAEEF8ED6288FF47" author="Lowry JK" lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="40" pageNumber="74" pagination="183 - 211" refId="ref31036" refString="Lowry JK. 1981. The amphipod genus Cerapus in New Zealand and subantarctic waters (Corophioidea, Ischyroceridae). Journal of Natural History 15: 183 - 211." type="journal article" year="1981">Lowry, 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the long thin antennae, about half the body length, and the dactylus of gnathopod 2 more than half the propodus length. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName id="B7E6BCC59A16B11FFDCFFEB060B8FE83" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Berents" authorityYear="1996" box="[629,759,259,281]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="42921B549A16B11FFDCFFEB060B8FE83" box="[629,759,259,281]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a slender palp of the mandible and seven robust setae on the outer plate of maxilla 1; however, 
<taxonomicName id="B7E6BCC59A16B11FFF2AFEEB62B1FEEF" authority="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo, 2014" authorityName="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo" authorityYear="2014" box="[144,254,351,372]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teresae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="42921B549A16B11FFF2AFEEB62B1FEEF" box="[144,254,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. teresae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="59A1A62F9A16B11FFEBCFEEB6315FEEF" box="[262,346,351,372]" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from both species by the 2-articulate flagellum of antenna 1, the distoventral process of gnathopod 2 more produced anteriorly, and a more inflated propodus. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="B7E6BCC59A16B11FFF2AFE6E62B1FE74" authority="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo, 2014" authorityName="Souza-Filho &amp; Serejo" authorityYear="2014" box="[144,254,474,495]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teresae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="42921B549A16B11FFF2AFE6E62B1FE74" box="[144,254,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. teresae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="59A1A62F9A16B11FFEBCFE6E6315FE74" box="[262,346,474,495]" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B7E6BCC59A16B11FFE53FE6E6024FE75" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Berents" authorityYear="1996" box="[489,619,473,495]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Notopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="42921B549A16B11FFE53FE6E6024FE75" box="[489,619,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">N. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of eyes, absence of pleopod 3, the inner ramus of uropod 3 about two-thirds the outer ramus length, and the telson weakly cleft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7059C7469A16B11FFF2AFDDE63EEFDE4" blockId="41.[144,758,618,701]" box="[144,417,618,639]" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="42921B549A16B11FFF2AFDDE63EEFDE4" box="[144,417,618,639]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="75">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
